Apr 22 2009 	Good hotel in great location.	If you are looking to get the real Dubai experience and not a beach resort holiday Landmark plaza is in a excellent location. The hotel provides a good service with clean and spacious rooms. Make sure you get a room with a balcony to experience the beauty of Al Nasser Square. The hotel is just minutes from the bazaars and souks as well as the water front. Taking a cab to and from the airport cost about 30 dirhams and geting to Jumeriah beach cost roughly the same. Diera city centre is a quick 5 minute cab ride costing 5-7 dirhams. Eatting around the hotel is very diverse with plenty of local cheap food (shawarmas) and a McDonalds across the street. The hotel offers air conditioning, fridge with refreshments, tv, tourist information, breakfast and ironing facilities.	
Mar 4 2009 	So central	Very good hotel. Room overlooked Nasser Square and had a view of the Creek. Walking distance to all hotel bars &amp; restaurants, also to the Gold Souk. A courtesy bus was put on to take you to the beach and to collect you.	
Mar 2 2009 	A Good Standard 3 Star Hotel	A good 3star Hotel. apartt from 1 Hiccup over rooms when we arrived it really was to a good standard. the main disadvantage was that a new Metro Station is being built right outside. hardly the Hotels fault. It is central for Shopping with plenty of good Restaurants nearby =even Mc D's opposite and Kentucky next door. Also close to Red Bus Pick up, and the Creek. The room was large with Balcony and clean, with Beds changed daily. As with all over Bath Showers the water does run across the top of the Bath and drip to the floor. You willl reads moans about this, but it is easily remided, just ask the Cleaner for an extra mat and put it on the top of the Bath - no problem. It is a Cosmopolitan Hotel with many Nationalities from Ghanains to Russians. But no worse the thre Hotels in Sharm. We found most of the Russians pleasant people.I would reccomend the Hotel, as long as you are not expecting a Beach Holiday,although there is a Minibus daily to the Beach. You should do the Red Bus Tour lthough fairly expensive at 150aed each(30 pst). the Beach tour is good. One thing to remember it finishes at 5.00pm. You could be left at City Gate with a Taxi ride. Again not expensive about 2pst. Last thing do take the evening trip on the Floating Restaurants which leave from the Creek. At 150aed each it is well worth the money. The Plaza is a good standard 3 Star Hotel - Just dont look for 5 Star surroundings	
