Jun 29 2006	Great Location reasonable price - recommended	I stayed last week for a few nights at the Landmark Hotel in Dubai and was quite pleased with what I got for the money. The room was spacious, clean and had everything you needed including very effective aircon, TV, I even had a seperate little lounge room although I travelled alone. Bathroom was also clean and spacious - no problems there. The only thing one could complain about was the fact that the room had only one small window and a view of some roofs - but hey, I didn't come there to stay in the room and look out the window. As others have mentioned, the location is great to explore the &quot;old&quot; part of Dubai and the verious Souks. It's only a 5 minute walk to Dubai Creek where you can catch a boat across for pennies. There are also plenty of interesting shops in the area and good cafes where one can get great food at very reasonable prices.I didn't fancy the hotel restaurant much, as you can get better food cheaper within easy walking distance in any direction. Give the Macdonald's and KFC nearby a miss and try some of the local food - it's well worth it. The transfer from the hotel to the airport isn't free, and costs only a little less than a taxi.No one stared at me, even in the pool, but being a big boofy bloke, I'd have been worried if they did. Overall, great location, rather decent room, ok service - better than what I expected for the price, I'd stay there again.	
Apr 29 2006	Ideal!	I stayed in the Landmark for 8 nights and it was perfect. The room was very clean and had aircon/TV/good shower/hairdryer etc. The staff were friendly when spoken to if a little bit shy initially. The Hotel on a whole is not as grand as some of the others in the area but you get what you pay for. I had laundry done and it came back immaculately ironed and cleaned. Had breakfast in bed a couple of times which was delicious, very generous helpings and reasonable. The Hotel has a very nice chinese restaurant and a couple of very good shops. It is situated in the perfect place for the electric shops and is in an ideal location to get taxis to all of the shopping malls and Jumeriah beach. The taxis are very reasonable also. Yes, the men do stare at you but this is not the Hotel's fault! If you feel a bit peckish and want something quick there is a Kentucky Fried Chicken and a MacDonalds within 2 minutes walking distance!!The Hotel has a very good gym and changing rooms and a massage service is also available. The pool is very small but clean and not many people use it so it is ideal for sitting around and reading a book in peace, although as it is on the roof it gets extremely hot but the water is very cool and there is a water dispenser nearby.This Hotel is perfect for the budget traveller and is the best budget Hotel in the area. The Hotel in on par with a travel lodge or similar in Britain. In my opinion I don't think some of the negative reviews on this website are fair as this Hotel is very good for the price. I would definitely stay there again.	
